Commentary: what a way to start the match! Fullish length, around middle and leg, and he swings this over square leg, and wayyyyyyyyyy into the lower portion of the stands
Commentary_short: Holder to Hazratullah Zazai, SIX runs

Commentary: length, pitches outside leg and comes off his pad as he shapes to flick. A bit of extra pace and bounce from Holder
Commentary_short: Holder to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: shorter, straighter, and he goes back and punches this towards cover. Thought of a quick single, but the fieldsman was quick to converge on it
Commentary_short: Holder to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: short, and he has hooked this away towards deep backward square leg. The ball sat up and begged to be punished, and Zazai obliged
Commentary_short: Holder to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: fuller, and he backs away and looks to go over covers. Off the edge, and flies off over short third man, but pulls up short of the boundary
full toss, and he has driven this straight back past the bowler. What a start for Zazai!
Commentary_short: Holder to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: length, but starts from outside leg, and a touch of swing further down the leg side. Gurbaz walks across the stumps, and misses out. Called wide
length, a bit of width, and he cuts this hard, but straight along the ground to point
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: short, angles into him, and he tucks this away towards short fine leg. Easy single, as the fielder has to move across to his left
shortish length, and he swings this away towards deep square leg. Protection there for Cottrell, which enables them to go through for a comfortable single
length, bounces away as it angles across him, and beats the outside edge! Gurbaz was looking perhaps to get the upper cut going, but missed out
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: length, and he bashes this hard into the ground and towards cover
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: length, outside off, and he swings across the line and gets an outside edge! Goes high, but far enough to go beyond the wicketkeeper, and plonks on the surface close to third man. They scurry back for the second
good ball! Just a little back of good length, and nips across him, and eludes the outside edge as Zazai looks to run it towards third man. Great carry through to Ramdhin
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: length, around middle and leg, angles across him, and he pushes this towards cover
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: full, wide, and he has swung this over the infield through the off side. Another boundary for Zazai, as he picks the slower ball from Williams
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, FOUR runs

Commentary: quicker, tucks him up by angling this from just outside leg. It goes off the inside edge and drops towards fine leg. Good call from the non-striker fetches them a single
length, angles in, and he plays it with the incoming movement to the right of short mid-wicket. Good running again between the two batsmen
length, angles away, and he looks to run it towards third man. Fielded by gully, who is the only man catchng behind the wicket on the off side now
Commentary_short: Williams to Hazratullah Zazai, no run

Commentary: length, angles away from him, and he plays it to the right of short third man. They set off immediately and go through for a single. A bit of a misfield from Walsh there, otherwise it could have been close

DROPPED! Length ball, outside off, and he swings this looking to bash it down the wicket. The ball flies off the top edge, and runs to the right of Denesh Ramdhin. Kesrick Williams comes flying in, and flicks it off the waiting gloves of Ramdhin, and it bounces off his arms and lands towards fine leg. There's a bemused expression all around, as Zazai survives a terrible shot!
length, angles in, and he drives this back down the wicket
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, no run

Commentary: short, and he has gone for a full-blooded pull. Off the edge again, and this time it runs away towards fine leg
this is gorgeous! Slightly fuller in length from Cottrell, and the line angles across him, and towards the off stump, but he clears his front leg and whips this towards long on
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: a virtual replay of the previous ball! Full and straighter this time from Cottrell, and he plays this whippy flick-drive again, and just about clears mid on this time
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Rahmanullah Gurbaz, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball, full, and he moves away and drives this a bit to the left of mid off. They are able to get through for a single

another full-blooded shot, but this time Williams has struck! Fuller from Williams, but a change of pace too, and Gurbaz looks to go towards long on again. Skews the shot towards deep mid-wicket, and it's Pollard who tracks back and gets under it. It went miles in the air, and Pollard did well to hold on after an initial juggle
Dismissal_text: Rahmanullah Gurbaz c Pollard b Williams 15 (12b 2x4 0x6) SR: 125.00

Commentary: two in two! Slower ball again from Williams, and tossed up a bit wider this time for Zazai, and he checks an intended drive, and it goes straight towards cover-point
Dismissal_text: Hazratullah Zazai c King b Williams 26 (15b 3x4 1x6) SR: 173.33

Commentary: shorter ball, and he swings this away towards deep square leg
slower ball, full, and he drives this towards mid on. Asghar Afghan wants a single, but is asked to rush back, as that travels quickly
Commentary_short: Williams to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: length, width, and he backs away and spanks this through covers
Commentary_short: Williams to Karim Janat, FOUR runs

Commentary: length on the stumps, moving inwards, flicked off the pads to short fine leg
Commentary_short: Holder to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: fuller, still angling into the batsman and he tucks it to deep square leg
length outside off, squirted to short third man
Commentary_short: Holder to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: goes shorter this time, and Janat controls the pull to play it to short fine leg. Can't beat the fielder so no runs
Commentary_short: Holder to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: picked the gap nicely this time. Width outside off and a bit short, he flashes a cut and finesses the gap between point and short third man
Commentary_short: Holder to Karim Janat, FOUR runs

Commentary: the typical fast bowler response, a bouncer dug in very short, goes over the batsman's left shoulder. Holder a bit lucky to get away with that perhaps, could have been a wide
Commentary_short: Holder to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: length outside off, steered to backward point
Commentary_short: Paul to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: slows the pace up a bit, on a length on the stumps, he waits for it and turns it to deep midwicket
floats up a wide yorker outside off, and he gets low down to slap it to wide mid-off
back of a length on middle and off, turned to short fine leg off the back foot. Soft hands so there's enough time for a quick single
mixes it up with a bouncer, but it's not a pacy one, and he waits for it before pulling it from in front of his helmet and keeping the ball down, through midwicket
another short ball, this one didn't rise as much and sat up, he rocks back and pulls powerfully through midwicket. There's a fielder there so he cleans up
full toss outside off, leathers this to cover. Hit very hard indeed but Pollard at short cover manages to get a hand to it and takes the momentum off the ball. That would have stung.
down the track, gets to the pitch and punches an off-drive. Flat one that bounces well before long-off
better length from Hayden Walsh, not full enough to invite the drive. He goes back to cut but misses the ball
Commentary_short: Walsh to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: length outside off, spinning away, pushed into the offside
and Asghar has made a conscious decision to attack the leggie. Shimmies down the track again and whacks this one straight, but it hits the stumps at the other end
Commentary_short: Walsh to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: goes back to cut this length ball but doesn't connect, and he's mighty upset with himself. He's hit two powerful shots in the over that, on another day, could have fetched 8 runs. Today, just 1 run.
Commentary_short: Walsh to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: length outside off, cuts it through point
yorker on the stumps, he goes deep in his crease to try and helicopter it away, but ends up hitting it into his pad and it rolls back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Holder to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: good yorker again, from slightly wide of the crease and homing in on middle stump. Digs it back out to the bowler
Commentary_short: Holder to Asghar Afghan, no run

Commentary: Asghar is not going to be happy looking at that replay. Short ball, went past him down the legside at chest height, he was trying to hit it too hard while moving across to pull, ends up getting a feather and Ramdhin takes an excellent catch, diving to his left. That ball could have been put away for four, but the accumulated dot balls led to poor execution
Dismissal_text: Asghar Afghan c †Ramdin b Holder 8 (14b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

Commentary: back of a length in the channel, defended towards cover-point
Commentary_short: Holder to Ibrahim Zadran, no run

Commentary: good length angling into him and straightens a touch, defended solidly back
Commentary_short: Holder to Ibrahim Zadran, no run

Commentary: looking to go inside out, but gets a thick outside edge that runs down to the third man boundary. Nicely tossed up, he was making room, but the ball turned more than he expected
Commentary_short: Walsh to Karim Janat, FOUR runs

Commentary: quicker one, on a length outside off, he goes to cut but doesn't connect
Commentary_short: Walsh to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: length outside off, slaps it towards cover and Pollard dives to his left to stop it
Commentary_short: Walsh to Karim Janat, no run

Commentary: just over point and finds the fence. Living dangerously is Janat. This one turned a fair bit but was shorter, allowing him time to rock back and slash it, but he didn't time it perfectly. Point was jumping up but it went just over
Commentary_short: Walsh to Karim Janat, FOUR runs

Commentary: and that's the most convincing shot of the over. Tossed up outside off, too full, he gets down on one knee and corks an extra cover drive that clears the in-field.
Commentary_short: Walsh to Karim Janat, FOUR runs

Commentary: walks into the flick to an over-pitched ball and plays it softly enough into midwicket to get a well-run two
back of a length in the channel, defended to point off the back foot
Commentary_short: Holder to Ibrahim Zadran, no run

Commentary: length ball angling into him, pushed towards mid-on. Tight line
Commentary_short: Holder to Ibrahim Zadran, no run

Commentary: goes for the yorker on leg stump, but fractionally short and he pushes a straight on-drive to get off the mark

rapped on the pads, feet rooted to the crease and the umpire upholds his appeal. That came in very sharply off a length and Janat's shot selection was completely awry looking to push it but with his eight back when he should have been forward, but he's been a bit unlucky here because it looks like that would have gone down leg. Height also a possible issue.
Dismissal_text: Karim Janat lbw b Holder 26 (18b 5x4 0x6) SR: 144.44

Commentary: back of a length outside off, pushed to point
Commentary_short: Holder to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: defended towards cover
Commentary_short: Holder to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: length outside off, punched to deep extra cover
good length on a tight line outside off, steered to point
Commentary_short: Pollard to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: fuller outside off, looking to give himself room and flay this over cover but gets a thick edge that flies down to third man

length ball on middle and leg, he walks forward and tucks it to square leg. The fielder there - Keemo Paul - sprints in and fires in a throw. Pollard had not got back to the stumps, otherwise would have been tight
back of a length outside off, pushed towards cover
Commentary_short: Pollard to Ibrahim Zadran, no run

Commentary: slows it up, back of a length outside off, and the batsman who was looking to come down the track has to adjust and play this off the back foot backward of square
up and over. Held his shape nicely on that. Length ball outside off, and he unleashes a lofted straight drive. Didn't quite time it perfectly but got it enough to just carry over the rope
Commentary_short: Paul to Ibrahim Zadran, SIX runs

Commentary: foxed him with a slower bouncer. He was looking to pull but has to drop his wrists and decide against playing a shot while letting it go through
Commentary_short: Paul to Ibrahim Zadran, no run

Commentary: excellent catch by Pollard at short cover. Another good change of pace by Keemo, and he has Ibrahim playing the cover drive too early. Ends up popping it in the air and Pollard, injured finger and all, takes a good low catch in front of him, tumbling forward.
Dismissal_text: Ibrahim Zadran c Pollard b Paul 11 (12b 0x4 1x6) SR: 91.66

Commentary: back of a length on the fourth stump, steered to third man, staying beside the ball and hanging on the back foot
short ball, he ducks under it. It's called a no-ball for height.
Commentary_short: Paul to Najibullah Zadran, 1 no ball

Commentary: went for the wide ball outside off but it's just outside the tram line, so it's still a free hit
angling into him, swung away hard but without timing and it goes to deep midwicket
fuller on the stumps, clipped to short midwicket
Commentary_short: Paul to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: scoots through under his big swing, outside off. He wanted to send this to cow corner, but connected with air
Commentary_short: Pollard to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: tries to mix it up by bowling it wide of off stump but it ends up beyond the tram line and he'll have to rebowl that. Marginal call, Pollard's not too happy with it
fuller on the stumps, tucked towards square leg for a single
slows it up, length ball angling into him, tucked to deep square leg
fuller on the pads, clipped backward of square
rolls his fingers over that one, slower length ball on off, bunted back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Pollard to Mohammad Nabi, no run

Commentary: goes very wide of the crease and angles it full on the stumps, clipped off his pads to wide long-on

spoons a catch to mid-off. You've to create all the pace by yourself on this surface and the West Indians have been bowling cleverly, with changes of pace. This one sticks in the pitch on a length, Nabi wanted to go big, but ends up hitting it too early, gets more height than distance - and not even that much height - for an easy catch.
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Nabi c Williams b Paul 3 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: fuller on middle stump, flicked away but short midwicket is in place and fields it
Commentary_short: Paul to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: another slower one, out of the back of the hand, on a length in the stump line, and he can only pat it back down the pitch
Commentary_short: Paul to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: fuller, clipped off his toes with a flourish to long-on
normal pace ball, outside off and that's a good shot, cut through point. There's a fielder there who runs to his left, slides and stops
good follow up with a surprise bouncer that he ducks under. Wasn't expecting that
Commentary_short: Paul to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: another slower ball, length outside off, worked backward of square
fuller outside off, glides it to third man
angling into him from a bit wider of the crease, punches it to long-on
digs it into the pitch but it sticks and doesn't come on, he has to wait and flick it to short fine leg

that one came back in sharply from outside off, bowled at normal pace - which his a good variation given the mode of slower balls - and Gulbadin is caught by surprise. Ends up in an awkward position while trying to cut it but being hit above the waist
Commentary_short: Williams to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: length outside off, steered to point
Commentary_short: Williams to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: short outside off, but no pace on the ball again, pulls it to deep midwicket without timing
valuable runs for Afghanistan and good shot. Too short and he swivels and pulls it backward square leg. Hit it well enough and didn't bother to keep it down, bounces down into the boundary
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Gulbadin Naib, FOUR runs

Commentary: freebies from West Indies. Cottrell loses his radar and bowls it well down leg. Ramdhin had moved in place but somehow misses it, didn't' judge the bounce and it went below his gloves. Five wides
back of a length outside off, he opens his shoulders and slaps it back past the bowler, very straight
normal pace, length ball outside off, swatted to deep midwicket, playing across the line
pacy bouncer. gets it to climb a bit and he's a bit late on that, pulls it to long-on
angling into him and he squirts it backward of square
that's nicely played, flays a square drive through cover. There is protection in the deep though. This was too short and a bit too wide outside off
yorker length on the stumps, into him from around the wicket. He wants to go straight but gets a thick leading edge that flies to wide long-on. drops well short
back of a length, he swats a pull shot to long-on, but got it off the toe end of the bat
top shot. Slower off-cutter banged in too short, he rides the bounce and flays it over extra cover's head. Good timing and placement
Commentary_short: Paul to Gulbadin Naib, FOUR runs

Commentary: normal pace ball, fuller nibbling around off, pushed to the bowler's left on the front foot
yorker on the stumps, goes deep in his crease and drives to long-off
length ball on the stumps, goes back and whacks a pull across the line to deep midwicket
saw him going across the line, and bowled it wide of off, off-cutter moving away, and not full enough to swing towards cow corner. Misses it
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Gulbadin Naib, no run

Commentary: angling into him, this time he was looking to give himself room but he ends up inside edging onto pad and it rolls towards slip
length outside off, smacked hard but without timing, with a horizontal bat to wide long-on
fullish, flicked to square leg
super shot. Full on the stumps, and he connects really well with his heave to cow corner, pings off the bat and flies over the boundary
Commentary_short: Cottrell to Gulbadin Naib, SIX runs

Commentary: back of a length in the channel, wants to smack it across the line but misses it
Commentary_short: Williams to Najibullah Zadran, no run

Commentary: slower ball on the pads, tried to slog it over square but no timing, edged onto pad and trickles away

tries to do too much while the bowler keeps it simple and wins the contest. Gulbadin well across to try and paddle it fine, but Williams kept it full and cutting in. Gulbadin has one leg on the tramline and one in line with the stumps trying to pull off the shot, he misses and the leg in line with the stumps is hit
Dismissal_text: Gulbadin Naib lbw b Williams 24 (18b 2x4 1x6) SR: 133.33

Commentary: clears his front leg and smacks a pull straight, but without timing. Pollard at mid-off collects on the bounce
yorker outside off, driven to extra cover
short ball outside off, had the width to cut, not exactly where he intended to send it, but he gets it a bit finer than he wanted to and it goes to the third man boundary. Got a little big on him
Commentary_short: Williams to Rashid Khan, FOUR runs

Commentary: length outside off, punched to cover
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to King, no run

Commentary: fuller, angling into him, driven uppishly to the bowler's left. Hung in the air a bit
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to King, 2 runs

Commentary: angling into him, flicked off his pads to midwicket's left
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to King, 1 run

Commentary: length ball spinning away a touch, defended on the front foot. Rolls off a thick outside edge
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, no run

Commentary: beaten outside off, had a waft at it without moving his feet much and it spun past. uh oh, there was a faint nick there when it went past the bat, so it'll go down as as drop. Went quickly to the keeper, bounced off his glove and to his left. Slip was too deep to be able to take it
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, no run

Commentary: defended towards cover on the front foot
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, no run

Commentary: too short and too wide outside off, could free his arms and slash this through point for a boundary
length outside off, punched to cover
length ball coming into him, takes the pace off, clipped to midwicket
rocks back, swivels and pulls this to the deep square leg boundary for a one-bounce four. Marginally short again, but sits up and Lewis is in form, he's not going to miss out on that
change of pace, similar length but doesn't come on as well and Lewis mis-times his pull. the ball pops in the air but falls short of mid-on
full outside off, walks into the on-drive, but can't beat mid-on
fuller on the stumps, lunges out and defends
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to King, no run

Commentary: full on off again, flicked on the front foot through midwicket
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to King, 1 run

Commentary: length outside off, cuts it to short third man's left
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, no run

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, goes to sweep but doesn't connect. Loud appeal, not given. Sliding down
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, no run

Commentary: is a bit late to transfer weight back, and ends up awkwardly slapping it towards mid-off
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: length on the stumps, flicked to long-on
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to King, 1 run

Commentary: floats up a slower ball on the stumps, and he waits for it, and flicks it to midwicket's left
how did that miss! Off-cutter and he hasn't read it, tries to swat across the line, it goes under the bat and is very close to off stump on the way to the keeper
normal pace, back of a length cutting into him, squirted to short third man

pace off the ball again, well outside off, he goes hard at it and slaps it to mid-off from the toe-end. Asghar has to run to his right - he's a bit wide - and slide to stop it. He doesn't do that and it bounces off him and allows the batsmen a second run

knocked him over. Another off-cutter, this one is bowled on a tighter line and a fuller length. King had no clue about that, was heaving across the line way too early. He misses, the bowler hits flush on middle stump.
good length, on a tight off-stump line, tucked off his pads to deep square leg
length angled into him, pushed towards midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Hetmyer, no run

Commentary: fuller on the stumps, worked to midwicket
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Hetmyer, no run

Commentary: too short outside off, and he transfers weight back nicely and punches it through cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Hetmyer, FOUR runs

Commentary: floated up on the stumps, pushed into the legside
good length, turns a bit and the batsman's hanging on the back foot, defends from the crease, rolls off the outside half of the bat back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, no run

Commentary: fuller and swept nicely to deep square leg
nearly got through him! The carrom ball, and he played back a touch, and got an inside edge. It went just past the stumps and went past the keeper
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, 1 run

Commentary: floated wide down the leg side, and Hetmyer shuffles across to flick but cannot lay bat on it
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Hetmyer, 1 wide

Commentary: goes back to punch one angling into him towards cover
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Hetmyer, no run

Commentary: shorter, angles into him, and he hangs back and flicks this towards deep square leg
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Hetmyer, 1 run

Commentary: this could be close! Shuffles across to sweep a ball pitched around off stump. Misses the ball completely, and they appeal loudly as they cut through for a leg-bye to short fine leg. Perhaps impact is just outside off, but that was close
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, 1 leg bye

Commentary: flicks this towards short fine leg. Asghar Afghan has to move across to his right, and they pick up a quick single
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Hetmyer, 1 run

Commentary: defends a ball slanting in from wide of the crease, straight back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Lewis, no run

Commentary: length, and he goes back and whips this towards deep mid-wicket
length, outside off, and he presses forward and plays it with soft hands towards short third man
hangs back and cuts a shorter ball towards the sweeper at the deep point boundary
length, and he punches this towards cover
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, no run

Commentary: length, and he walks across and wants to flick. Surprised by some extra bounce, and ends up skewing an attempted paddle shot. Goes in the air, but well short of deep square leg

goes back and plays this with soft hands towards mid-wicket. There's acres of space there, and he wants two, but Nabi is very quick to get to the ball after his follow-through, and he is able to prevent a second
short of a length, angles across, and he plays it back down the wicket
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Hetmyer, no run

Commentary: full ball, and given out leg-before! Did that pitch within the leg-stump line? It's a tricky one, but that's a good breakthrough for Afghanistan. Fuller, and a touch quicker, and Hetmyer justifiably shuffles across to try and flick this away. Beaten for pace, but at first glance, it did seem that this ball had pitched outside leg. To be fair, Janat himself had got a dodgy decision against Holder when he was batting, so this almost evens it out
Dismissal_text: SO Hetmyer lbw b Karim Janat 11 (13b 1x4 0x6) SR: 84.61

Commentary: beaten outside off! Just a tentative poke, as Janat pitches it up, and gets a bit of swing away
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: short, angles in, and he plays it towards mid-wicket
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: fuller, and he is able to drive this, leaning forward, towards long on
full ball, straightens a touch, and Lewis miscues an attempted straight drive, away towards cover
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Lewis, no run

Commentary: length, and he presses forward to defend. Wants one, but that lands too close to Nabi in his follow through
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: a touch shorter, and he goes back and whips this off his pads towards square leg
full, but down the leg side, and Lewis swings this around between short fine leg and deep square leg. Smart shot, as he used the pace and angle incoming towards him
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, FOUR runs

Commentary: skips down the wicket, and ends up taking a ball on the full. Drives it off the outer edge, and it is cut off by Naveen at point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Nabi to Lewis, no run

Commentary: hangs back and swings a flatter ball, straight into him, towards deep square leg. Cannot get this fine enough, and will only get one
length, and he presses forward and places this to the right of point. They go through for a single, and the bowler and the keeper aren't too happy that this single was completed so easily
slow off-cutter, pitching outside leg, and he flicks this towards deep square leg. The fielder has to come in from the deep, and that allows them to come through for two
shorter, angled across, and he plays it towards cover
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: length, just outside off, and he presses forward and defends this to the right of mid off. Quick single taken

short, and he looks to swing this across the line, and holes out to long on! Might have been a bit slower again, but it was a poor shot -- just had no shape as he looked to swat this away. Top edge, and it flew quite flat towards Ibrahim Zadran, who came in a few steps and took the catch comfortably
Dismissal_text: E Lewis c Ibrahim Zadran b Karim Janat 14 (22b 2x4 0x6) SR: 63.63

Commentary: seam-up, a touch fuller, straight, and Rutherford plays it straight back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Rutherford, no run

Commentary: another wicket for Janat! That's a ball that any fast bowler would have been proud off. Angles across him, full, and just a hint of movement off the seam. The line and length were such that Rutherford was sucked into poking at it. A healthy edge through to the keeper, as Karim Janat lets out a scream in delight. This is an inspired selection by Afghanistan today!
Dismissal_text: SE Rutherford c †Rahmanullah Gurbaz b Karim Janat 6 (11b 0x4 0x6) SR: 54.54

Commentary: length, and Pollard goes back to play it after it turns away a touch from him. Defended back down the wicket
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Pollard, no run

Commentary: well played! Flights this a little outside off, and Pollard takes the invitation, with a powerful drive uppish through extra cover
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Pollard, FOUR runs

Commentary: googly, and he goes back and flicks this towards deep square leg
length, and Ramdin goes back to defend this towards point, with the turn away from him
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: shorter, and he hangs back and drives this towards deep cover point
length, and he fetches this from outside off, and flicks it towards square leg. Rashid fields in his follow-through, with a slide for effect
uses his feet to advance down the track, even before Janat has bowled! Janat sticks to a good length, jagging back in, and Pollard can only defend
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Pollard, no run

Commentary: length, angles into him, and he plays it straight to mid-wicket. There's a direct hit from there, but he looks safe at first glance. It's been referred, but he was well in. Good energy on the field, nevertheless!
length, just from outside off, it angles back in and he defends
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: fuller, straighter, and he drives this towards long on

what a wicket! Janat in seventh heaven, as the finger goes up for a leg-before against Kieron Pollard. Fast ball, delivered from wide of the crease, but the line was spot-on, jagging back at Pollard, and giving him very little wriggle-room to get a shot going. The West Indies captain ended up playing from the crease, and the umpire has little hesitation in sending him on his way
Dismissal_text: KA Pollard lbw b Karim Janat 7 (7b 1x4 0x6) SR: 100.00

Commentary: full, outside off, and he drives this hard, but straight to point
flighted around off, and he drives this hard, taking it on the half-volley. Should have been stopped at cover, but Najib Zadran cannot take the sting off this
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Holder, FOUR runs

Commentary: shorter, leg-break, and he goes back and punches this towards cover
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Holder, no run

Commentary: flatter, shorter, and he goes back and punches this towards long on
length, and he goes back to punch this back to Rashid
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: wrong 'un, floated outside off. Ramdin goes for the drive, and gets it off the under edge. It eludes the stumps, though
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: length, plays it away between point and short third man. Wants a single, but that has travelled quite quickly
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: leg-cutter, short of a length, and he dabs this towards short third man. They run hard to complete the single
slower ball, nearly a donkey drop, and he hangs back and swings this around towards deep mid-wicket
slow leg-cutter, and forces Holder to fetch this from outside off towards long on. He'd cleared his leg and was in no position to go straight, as he inteded to initially
short, slow and he swings this towards deep mid-wicket
short, and he swings this towards fine leg. It wasn't far off from the man at short fine leg, but in the end, Holder got enough bat to clear the man there
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Holder, FOUR runs

Commentary: short, and he swings this towards deep mid-wicket

Rashid strikes! He's done him in with the line of that ball, and Gurbaz has done the rest. Holder pre-meditates this a bit, skipping down the wicket, possibly aiming to go straight down the wicket. Rashid goes flatter and wider, and turns it past his outside edge. Once Gurbaz collected, there was only going to be one result
Dismissal_text: JO Holder st †Rahmanullah Gurbaz b Rashid Khan 13 (9b 2x4 0x6) SR: 144.44

Commentary: length, and he has swung this from outside off, well into the mid-wicket fence! Top connection from Keemo Paul!
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Paul, SIX runs

Commentary: shorter, and he goes back and flicks this towards deep mid-wicket
short, and he goes back and flicks this towards mid-wicket
loud appeal for a caught-behind, but more from the keeper than Rashid, who joins in belatedly! Not given, as the ball spun past the outside edge as Ramdin stretched forward to defend
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Paul, no run

Commentary: length, turns away from him at good pace, and he can only defend this
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Paul, no run

Commentary: slower ball, full, around the stumps, and he hangs back to flick this towards mid-wicket
slower ball, on the stumps, and he backs away to the onside and ends up swinging across the line. Only towards deep mid-wicket
fuller, slower, and he flicks it away towards deep square leg
slower ball, fetched from outside off, and played towards long on. Paul unhappy with himself, for not being able to generate any pace or placement on this
slower ball, and he swings this hard from a middle and leg line, towards deep square leg
slow leg-cutter again, and he thrashes this down, one-bounce towards long on
backs away and swings this inside out towards extra cover. There's a fielder right there, though
fuller, and some good turn away from Ramdin. He swings in hope, looking for long on, and misses out on contact by a country-mile
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: fuller, wider, and dropped! It was hit back really hard, and he just got a hand to it, and it deflected away towards midwicket
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: another swing-and-a-miss. Full ball, and he looks for the slog sweep, but gets nothing on it
Commentary_short: Rashid Khan to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: drives one closer to him towards extra cover. Some hard running will fetch them two
moves across to the off side and tries to flog one fired down the leg side. Called wide
length, and he looks to slog this straight, but yet again the lack of pace means he has dragged this towards long on
slower ball, just outside off, and he plays it wide of cover for a single

five for Janat! Another full ball, just outside off, and Paul goes for an almight heave. Off the inside edge, and on to the base of off-stump. Janat is pumped, as he should be. It's been a fine team effort, but he is by far the Afghan individual that has stood out
Dismissal_text: KMA Paul  b Karim Janat 11 (9b 0x4 1x6) SR: 122.22

Commentary: looks to bowl a slower ball from the back of the hand, and gets it all wronng. Pitches well outside the tramlines on the off side
full, and just outside off, and Walsh hits this towards extra cover
full, and he plays it back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: wide outside off, and drives to cover. Takes the fielder on, and a direct hit would have been close, but he gets through
length, played towards point. Wants a single, but turned back
Commentary_short: Karim Janat to Walsh, no run

Commentary: short ball, outisde off, and he has cut this away over short third man. Too little, too late, one would think...
fuller, angles into him, and he plays this towards deep square leg. Janat is the fielder to get to it first
slower ball, angles across him, and he plays at this a bit early. Misses it as it wobbles away to Gurbaz
fuller, faster, and he hits it hard into the ground, but straight back at the bowler
short, moving away from Walsh, who looks to back away to the on side, and ends up looking at an ungainly heave across the line
slower ball, around leg stump, and he swings this towards deep mid-wicket. Fielded by the man at deep square leg
short, slow and he hits it hard but back towards the bowler
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Ramdin, no run

Commentary: short, and he moves across the crease and gets it down towards fine leg. No protection there for Naib
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Ramdin, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower, short ball, and he swings this again in the same direction. Takes more of the edge and goes towards long leg as a result. One bounce to the fielder stationed there
slower ball, outside off. A bit too wide outside off, and called a wide
fuller, still wide outside off, and Walsh has a mighty swing at it. Nowhere near the ball
Commentary_short: Gulbadin Naib to Walsh, no run

Commentary: length, slower ball, and he swings this across the line, and Rashid Khan takes it at the deep mid-wicket fence! Decent contact from Walsh, as he finally latches on to the slower one, but sends this higher than far enough, and Rashid calls early to take this ahead of the man at long on. Naib almost gets into his bodybuilder pose, with arms crossed, and then signals to Walsh that hitting him across the line for six was just not on
Dismissal_text: HR Walsh c Rashid Khan b Gulbadin Naib 3 (8b 0x4 0x6) SR: 37.50

Commentary: fuller ball, straight, and he plays this towards short mid-wicket, and Afghanistan have won!
